cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with optimization of source-channel codes, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of non-convex optimization methods derived from statistical physics, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The problem of optimizing source-channel codes also has applications in control systems (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and neural networks (cs.NE).
